    {
      "id": "note_v2_intro",
      "type": "note",
      "label": "V2 Multi-scope Notes",
      "position": {
        "x": 1994.6343694670059,
        "y": -923.4444968158211
      },
      "config": {
        "markdown": "**VoxPoser (decomposed, env-decoupled) \u2014 plan via GT snapshot + follow closed-loop**\n\n**Pre-loop**: `env_reset` (metadata only) \u2192 `obs_init` (`env_libero__observe_objects`, privileged GT snapshot) \u2192 `vp_init` (builds the 7-LMP runtime in the BACKEND process) \u2192 `vp_planner` (instruction \u2192 subtask list).\n\n**Outer scope** (per subtask): `obs_loop` re-observes a fresh GT snapshot each iter; `vp_plan_subtask` (`voxposer__plan_subtask`, local method node) runs the composer LMP + 5 voxel maps + path planner against that snapshot and returns a world-frame `trajectory` \u2014 WITHOUT driving the sim. `expand_for_settle` inserts gripper-settle holds.\n\n**Inner loop** (per waypoint): composite `waypoint_exec` FOLLOWS the trajectory closed-loop: `dispense_waypoint \u2192 plan_executor \u2192 env_libero__step_ee_pose` (OSC convergence on the real sim, gym control signals). Double-click to inspect.\n\nWhy the snapshot is sound: plan_subtask never steps the sim, so every env read during one plan sees a single static state \u2014 a frozen snapshot is semantically identical to the retired in-subprocess live-adapter reads. The only env coupling is the observe_objects/step_pose pair; the LMP stack itself is env-agnostic (workspace/nodesets/voxposer/).\n\nCross-scope IO: `runtime_handle` + `trajectory` in; `episode_success`/`step_index`/`waypoints_completed`/`inner_status` out."
      }
    },
